item.title: Happy family destroyed by ICE
item.description: Renee Good on the left, her wife in the center, her mother on the right. Posing in front of their wedding photos. I'm not going to post a picture of their children. She was a mother of three, a daughter and two sons. "That's my wife, I don't know what to do," her wife is saying in one of the videos showing the murderers. "I have a six-year-old at school... we're new here we don't have anyone. We need a doctor." They had recently moved to Minnesota from Colorado. Her murderers blocked a doctor on the scene from rendering aid, and used their vehicles to block an ambulance called to the scene until local police made them move their trucks. Renee Good was not involved with any protest or resistance movement, was not wanted by the police, and was a citizen. She was just driving after dropping her wife off, having just dropped their kid off at school.

item.title: Eyewitness
item.description:
The second half addresses the defense for the shooting that ICE is pushing
There is a video I've put in the comments that shows why filming is so important. In the video, the ICE agent who originally walked towards the passenger side of the car, shielding his face from a citizen outside of the car, continues around to the bonnet. When the two ICE officers who exit the ICE vehicle on the driver side attempt entry to the vehicle, the lady reverses and then goes to pull away. The agent who walked around on her blind side, the passenger side, while her attention is on the two agents who exited the vehicle to her left, now holds his ground in front of the car just long enough to claim that the vehicle headed towards him, even as (a) he was positioned close enough to the left hand side of the car to step out of the way as he shoots and (b) despite the fact that the vehicle is turning right as it moves forward, away from the agent. The witness is slightly ambiguous in his assertion as to which agent fired the shots, showing the importance of filming...preferably letterbox, keeping to a full shot wherever possible. Stay safe, but not at the cost of your freedom.

item.title: "Stand Ready to Activate" Is not enough.
item.description: Walz is making the suggestion that he will activate the National Guard. Bitch, ACTIVATE THEM NOW. I urge every single U.S. citizen to call his office demanding the following: The arrest of every single ICE Agent in Minneapolis to find and detain the shooter. The holding of the shooter in custody WITHOUT BAIL until trial. "Pending investigation" - it's what cops do to ordinary citizens accused of "significant" crimes. And above all, a PROPORTIONATE, FORCEFUL RESPONSE to ICE's actions. They are to be EXPELLED from the state. FBI can remain, but ICE cannot. DHS cannot remain, either, as they have shown a willingness to cover for the fuck-ups of their agencies and agents. THIS IS NO LONGER A GAME WHERE DEMOCRATS CAN GET AWAY WITH "VIOLENCE IS NOT THE ANSWER", WHILE REFUSING TO APPLY THE FULL FORCE OF THEIR ELECTED OFFICE IN DEFENSE OF THEIR CONSTITUENTS. They MUST leverage their state powers to defend their citizens from ICE and federal overreach, or citizens will end up deciding that some fed needs to get got. THIS IS A MOMENT IN TIME THAT REQUIRES ALL POSSIBLE PRESSURE TO BE BROUGHT TO BEAR. This is a moment that will decide how America stands or falls. EVERYBODY SHOULD DO THEIR GODDAMN PART. Edit: To make it extra duper super clear to the commenters - this post is about encouraging people to CALL THE GOVERNOR. Talking about the shooting itself here is simply repeating ad-nauseam what is already on the Front Page. What matters the most right now is FOCUS.
